article.headline: Princeton 53, Northwestern State 51
article.story: MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Luke Owings scored a season-high 19 points to lead Princeton to a 53-51 win over Northwestern State in the consolation game of the Pepsi Blue and Gold Classic hosted by Marquette. Princeton (5-3), which lost to North Dakota State on Friday, shot 55 percent from the field, and scored 24 points in the paint, mostly coming off backdoor cuts and drives. Northwestern State (4-4), which entered the game averaging 80 points, was led by Trey Gilder's 13 points, while Keithan Hancock added 11.
